HB 524 Original 2026 Regular Session Bayham
Abstract: Provides that no local law shall be enacted except by a bill introduced by a
legislator whose district includes the locality where the matter to be affected is
located, unless there is a vacancy within such a district.
Present constitution provides that no local or special law shall be enacted unless notice of
the intent to introduce a bill to enact such a law has been published on two separate days in
the official journey of the locality where the matter to be affected is situated. Provides for
time constraints. Provides for the content of the notice.
Proposed constitutional amendment retains present constitution.
Present constitution provides that no local or special law relative to the creation of a special
district shall be enacted unless notice of the intent to introduce such a bill has been published
on three separate days in the official journal of the locality where the special district is to be
situated. Provides for time constraints. Provides for the content of the notice.
Proposed constitutional amendment retains present constitution.
Proposed constitutional amendment provides that no local law shall be enacted except by a
bill introduced by a legislator whose district includes the locality where the matter to be
affected is situated, unless there is a vacancy within such a district.
Provides for submission of the proposed amendment to the voters at the statewide election
to be held on November 3, 2026.
(Amends Const. Art. III, §13)
